org.vle.aid.metadata
Class ThesaurusRepository

java.lang.Object
  org.vle.aid.metadata.ThesaurusRepository

public class ThesaurusRepository
extends Object

This class works on top of a regular Repository. It adds high level thesaurus operations for manipulating repositories that contain SKOS and SKOS Mapping. For documentation of the methods see ThesaurusRepositoryWS.

Author:
wrvhage

ThesaurusRepository

public ThesaurusRepository(String server_url,
                           String repository,
                           String username,
                           String password)
Parameters:
server_url - the URL of the meta-data server that will be queried (e.g. http://www.host.org:8080/sesame)
repository - the name of the repository or model in the meta-data server (e.g. mem-rdfs-db)
username - the username of the user to access the repository as used by the meta-data server (e.g. testuser)
password - the password of the user to access the repository as used by the meta-data server (e.g. opensesame)
